description:
Hello! Welcome to my channel. I created this channel to show a little bit about Montreal, Canada. I hope you enjoy it :)

Living in this city/country was a dream since 2010, and I feel glad to be here. Another fact about me is that I love those videos from many decades ago: 1900, 1910, 1920.. I love to see how everything was - The architecture, the vehicles, the people, their habits and everything - I feel amazed by how society changed so much. So I thought: Why not contribute for posterity? Making many videos of walks around this city (And probably another channel later, to put all my old and new videos of trips?). 
I am glad to contribute. It is also a way to bring people on walks, people that might not be able to travel, or even to go out from home (for health reasons for example). Hope you enjoy the content as much as I enjoy to make it!

If you liked, please subscribe!

I am a landscape photographer from the UK. Every week I go out on-location and make videos to try to inspire you to do the same. 

The only way to get better at photography is to just get out and shoot! So this year, I will be taking you out with me as I photograph different scenes on location every Thursday. 

2022 is all about landscape photography!

From nearly drowning my camera at Henrhyd Falls, to getting electrocuted on the Malvern Hills, it should be an entertaining year ... I'll also be teaching you something about photography every week in my videos.

My name is Mike Smith and I am a professional photographer and videographer. I have been a photographer since the mid 90's back when film was all the rage and I have been making short films and videos since 2008. 

For instagram, facebook and twitter, click on the links in the top right hand corner, or head over to my website at www.mikesmithphotography.com

description:
We describe us as creators. But what makes us different from each other?
It's the way how we see the World. How we composite. How we shoot. What stories we tell. It's all about the story. 

We are indie filmmakers. Indie doesn't mean "Indiana" or "Indian", it's a title - Independent. 

Everyone has a story which deserves to be told. And my job as an indie filmmaker is to tell it in the best possible visual way using the art of cinematography language. 

It's all about the light. Composition. Emotions and colours. Exposure. And the most important - The Story.

My weapons are Blackmagic Design Pocket Cinema Camera 4K ( BMPCC4K ), paired with MFT lenses of Lumix 12-35 and legendary portrait god Helios 44-2 58mm f/2 having the best bokeh. I use DJI Mavic 2 Pro drone to make aerial footage having solid quality, DJI Ronin S handheld gimbal stabilizer with dual handle grip and a little boy - DJI Osmo Mobile 3. All my post production and color grade are made in Davinci Resolve Studio Version.

Many legendary racers have dominated supercross, including Jeremy McGrath, Ricky Carmichael, James Stewart, Ryan Villopoto, Chad Reed, and Ryan Dungey.

Regarded as the king of action sports, Supercross has been described as one of the most physically demanding sports in the world. После этого, в большинстве случаев, 95% вопросов отпадают сами собой. Если, всё же, вопросы остались, попробуйте позже пересмотреть видео ещё раз - в спокойной обстановке и уделяя больше внимания деталям.

description:
This is a channel dedicated to uploading scenes with female characters in slow motion with deep voices from cartoons or anime.

Rules for submitting: Keep it on topic by only submitting scenes of animated female characters voiced by adult actresses in slow motion. We sometimes upload live-action scenes but much less frequently. 

We try to upload scenes exactly as they were found, but we can also edit scenes to include deep voices if you ask us to. There is a playlist that contains all our edited scenes if you would like to check which have been edited. Please make sure that the scene you are asking us to edit already includes slow motion and contains voices or else we'll have nothing to edit. 

If you find a show with a slo-mo scene try to include the name of the episode and timestamps of when it happens. This will make it much easier for us to find and upload. If you only suggest the name of a show or character with no further context, then it's unlikely that we'll upload anything.
